	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=609><span id= >Lasae</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>"I have to disagree with what many of you are saying. The number one role of a tank is to TAUNT"<br><br>While we strongly encouraged to do this, it is not always possible, especially with a Ranger around or a Wizard who unloads to quickly.<br><br>"the second role is to take damage and last is to inflict damage."<br><br>This is our primary role, in my humble opinion.<br><br>"To be a good taunter u have to be able to deal enough damage to pull them off the casters."<br><br>Taunting is closely connected to how close you are to a creature, how often you hit it, how often you stun it, and how you time your taunts<br><br>"After lvl 30 soloing is almost impossible and Monks and rogues do more damage as fighters and casters do more damage then all of us. SO u must be in a group afterlvl 30 and if u want to be on anyones list of group members u better be good at keeping the mobs of the casters."<br><br>You can solo after 30 and not impossible or almost impossible in any fashion.&nbsp;&nbsp;It merely requires knowing the right spots, though I strongly encourage all warriors to group.<br><br>"In all of my grouping experience i find that i agro more often then any of the small warrior races. with high str my attack is much higher than any of the smaller races and i hit much more often which does wonders for tuantnig."<br><br>No stat (strength/dex/stamina/agility) effects how often you hit a creature, it is purely level/skill based (and if you have a haste item of course).  Of course 1h weapons hit more often and are more taunt effective than 2h weapons.  The reason you may be taunting "better" is your slam attack bumps you up on the "Aggro" list.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
